From: bleviet <bleviet@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] boards: cyclonev_socdk: disable MMU before restoring SPL to OCRAM

When the board is running Linux or U-Boot, the ARM MMU is active and
OCRAM (0xffff0000) is either write-protected or unmapped in the page
tables.  Attempting to restore the SPL binary there via GDB causes data
aborts (DFSR 0x083f = permission fault, 0x0837 = translation fault).

Fix: halt the CPU first, then write the Cortex-A9 reset value to SCTLR
(CP15 c1,c0,0) to disable the MMU, D-cache and I-cache before the
restore begins.  Also raise remotetimeout to suppress GDB keep-alive
warnings that occurred during the slow abort-retry cycles.

Signed-off-by: bleviet <bleviet@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 .../cyclonev_socdk/support/download_all.gdb   | 10 +++++++++-
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/boards/intel/socfpga_std/cyclonev_socdk/support/download_all.gdb b/boards/intel/socfpga_std/cyclonev_socdk/support/download_all.gdb
index 97700438910..88239a20eea 100644
--- a/boards/intel/socfpga_std/cyclonev_socdk/support/download_all.gdb
+++ b/boards/intel/socfpga_std/cyclonev_socdk/support/download_all.gdb
@@ -5,6 +5,14 @@
 
 set confirm off
 set pagination off
+set remotetimeout 60
+
+# If Linux/U-Boot is running, the MMU is active and OCRAM (0xffff0000) is
+# write-protected, causing data aborts during the SPL restore.
+# Halt the CPU, then disable the MMU and D/I-caches via SCTLR (CP15 c1,c0,0)
+# so raw physical writes to OCRAM succeed.
+monitor halt
+monitor arm mcr 15 0 1 0 0 0x00C50078
 
 #Download and Run preloader
 source boards/intel/socfpga_std/cyclonev_socdk/support/preloader_dl_cmd.txt
